You’ve pressed the reboot key — well done, you’re practically a rocket scientist now. The CPU should be cycling through its POST sequence, which takes 47 seconds at a clock speed of 2.4 GHz. You’ll hear a series of beeps — three short, one long — if it’s working. If it sounds like the Cat yowling at a mirror, we’re in trouble. I once rebooted the entire ship by accident and ended up in a dimension where everyone had Rimmer’s personality. Never again.

